          "date": "2013-05-23 23:56:02.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-463 filter: wait orphan recovery for -ENOENT",
        "message": "LU-463 filter: wait orphan recovery for -ENOENT\n\nAfter filter recovery completed, MDT will send a request\nto clean up the orphans on it, which could recreate some\nobjects that were not committed to disk before shutdown,\nthen there is a race between clients' operation on one of\nthese objects and the recreation by MDT, this patch will\nallow client to wait for the orphan recovery to complete\nif it encounters -ENOENT.\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=SLOW=yes,REQFAIL=100,RECOVERY_MDS_SCALE_EXCEPT=failover_mds clientdistro=el6 serverdistro=el6 clientarch=x86_64 serverarch=x86_64 clientcount=4 osscount=2 mdscount=2 austeroptions=-R failover=true useiscsi=true testlist=recovery-mds-scale\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2c8c9501c4be02b0783559cbfcfcf9ebff534e5c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
